data.identificationRemarks: Spent 160 mins waiting for this one to come out of the hole with @sandeepnanu. Very shy. Gave us the slip at least once. 3-4 feet long. Looks like a new individual. First reported at 10:30am. 4th image showing me waiting and the hole in the bottom left. 5th image showing hood pattern during capture. Released soon after nearby. Both of those by @sandeepnanu
Had eaten 1-2 toads. Released after a few hours. With @sandeepnanu

@sandeepnanu's first ever cobra rescue. Last photo of hood during the release later that day. Recapture of this individual from July 2021 - https://www.inaturalist.org/observations/88916400 (identical hood patterns, similar personalities. Had grown considerably!)

data.occurrenceRemarks: Was captured by local snake catcher and then released in the nearby forest
